metadata.name: Qualia #43
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

'Qualia' are personal instances of conscious experience; for example what it 'feels' like to see a color, or a shape.

Each image in this project is designed to provoke a personal experience of color and form.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x1500px PNG.

metadata.name: Treasured Rug #62
metadata.description:
A form of concrete poetry depicting a rug.
Typography created by multiple lines of typewriter text.
Features one of five possible character sets.
One of ten possible palettes for text color
90% chance of black paper, or 10% chance of white
10% chance of rare "Wild" character shift, otherwise 45% of either "Loose" or "Tight"
15% chance each of either rare "Narrow" or "Wide" rug otherwise "Standard"
3 styles of paper grain
Differing line gaps
Differing types of skew effect
Differing types of blend effect when characters overlay.

Press S to save in High Resolution

Uses p5.js and scribble.js
@p1x3lboy August 2022

metadata.name: Cuts #138
metadata.description:
Cuts is an abstract representation of the exact moments in our lives when something is cut. It could be moving to a different country, being fired, quitting a bad habit, when a relationship ends or when you receive a very bad (or good!) news.
By themselves, cuts are not positive or negative events; it really depends on who you were before and who you wish to be after. But one thing is sure: every cut creates a new space that wasn’t there. This space could be small or huge, ordered or chaotic, regardless, you have to deal with it. Sometimes cuts try to resist and heal themselves extruding the core of the fibres we are made of, but they will fail. A cut is irreversible and it’s up to us to fill the gap with meaning.

Main features include:
- Curated palettes (21)
- Drawing modes (3)
- Extrusions (yes/no)
- Orientation (3)
- Overlapping (yes/no)
- Covered area (2)
- Cut position (2)

In live mode:
- Press [s] to save a 2400x2400 px image
- Press [t] to toggle shading (sometimes flat colours rock!)
- Press [c] to see copyright notice
- Press [f] to log features in console

By Todemashi 2022
NFT License 2.0

### NOTES
Made with p5js and GLSL shaders.
Shaders are based on tutorials and code by Patricio Gonzalez Vivo - The Book of Shaders - https://thebookofshaders.com/

metadata.name: Metropolis IX #108
metadata.description:
We divide spaces into smaller spaces which we conquer and live in our solitude. We call that Metropolis.

Started this piece as a rule based generative art. Simply the algorithm takes a rectangle and throws 2 random points inside it within defined x and y distances. Then using those 2 points, algorithm draws another rectangle and assigns letters to the corners of rectangle "A,B,C,D" starting from top left corner in clockwise direction. Then it starts to draw cells from inner rectangle's corner A to parent's corner A and goes on. Once 4 cells are created, it creates 4 more cells in between other cells, thus dividing a rectangle into 9 pieces. This is where "IX" comes from. Depending on the cell properties; algorithm assigns circles, triangles, lines and points to cells creating a city scape when certain parameters are given to the division algorithm.

There are 18 possible outcomes:
"Hazy Day" 13% probability (half of this style will come with slightly more color transition)
"Hazy Night" 10% probability
"Crystal Day" 11% probability
"Crystal Night" 5% probability
"Mondrian Day"  3% probability
"Mondrian Night" 3% probability
"Bauhaus Day" 3% probability
"Bauhaus Night" 3% probability
"1 Chroma Day" 4% probability (Multiple values of a single hue on a monochrome gradient)
"Mondrian Crystal Day" 3% probability
"Mondrian Crystal Night" 3% probability
"Monochrome Day" 3% probability 
"Monochrome Night" 4% probability 
"Vibrant Day" 12% probability
"Vibrant Night" 9% probability
"Rainbow Day' 5% probability
"Rainbow Night' 3% probability
"Chaotic Day"   3% probability (which takes pretty random parameters and 25% of this outcome has probability of creating very first coloring style of the project, see console for the hidden feature)




Press "1" to download 1000px height PNG
Press "2" to download 2000px height PNG
Press "3" to download 3000px height PNG
Press "4" to download 4000px height PNG
Press "5" to download 5000px height PNG
Press "6" to download 6000px height PNG
Press "7" to download 7000px height PNG
Press "8" to download 8000px height PNG
Press "9" to download 12000px height PNG
Press "m' to download 900x1600px PNG for mobile wallpaper

Use CTRL+SHIFT+C or CMD+SHIFT+C to open console for hidden features

Created from scratch with p5.js 
Murat Atimtay 2022 | @atimtay | www.muratatimtay.com

metadata.description:
A debug view of the underlying particulate algorithm of Atoms' Gaze and Quantum Folly. Refined as a gift for collectors.

Enjoy watching the structures form. Once it's fully rendered you can download a full resolution image of 3508 x 4961 px by ***double clicking/tapping***. At this size the piece is printable at A3 size at 300 dpi. If you're interested in acquiring a signed print please contact @KRANKARTA.

Created on Chrome desktop 103.0 on 2022-08-06 in javascript and GLSL. Results on other browsers/devices may vary.

metadata.name: Minima #234
metadata.description:
Minima is a study on focus and color. Playing with the idea of a simple composition of semicircles, either rotated up or down. The focus of the observer is moved with the use of gradual animation in the gradients and occasional circles and/or rectangles connecting the shapes together through color.

The name minima stems from the origins of the composition, mostly taking inspiration from minimalism in its use of a few elements to form a composition greater than the sum of its parts. Less is more, as they say.

The point at the bottom right of the canvas resembles the end of a sentence. Like reading a book, you process the canvas in a similar way, moving from what pops the most to what the least.

As the reader of this canvas I hope you observe what happens to your focus as the colors gradually move across the screen. The animations themselves are looping based on a noised sine wave, which gives them imperfections, imperfections you can observe.

----

Click / Tap on the bar at the bottom of the canvas to open up the GUI, used to export your minima into any format you want. Either .png or .svg. Ready for printing, if you desire.

ps. there might be a secret keyboard shortcut...

----

Minima,
Wouter Missler, 2022,
p5js + webgl.

metadata.name: Provence #305
metadata.description:
The south of France namely the Provence has a cultural history of being an inspiration for impressionists and post-impressionists in the past.
For me personally the Provence is the place i was spending long, peaceful holidays as a child within beautiful nature.
This work does not so much aim for being realistic, rather than give an impression or feeling for this wonderful landscape. 
There are just a few different elements and concepts and yet there is variety of fascinating results.
I really hope you will enjoy your minting.

Notes:
STARTUP AND RENDERING MAY TAKE SOME TIME. (Up to 1min)
Code was written in typescript.
The only used libraries were chroma.js and simplex-noise
